tweet: Since March 14, 2020 there have been 146,794 cases of COVID-19 in Allegheny County residents, 9,248 hospitalizations and 2,439 deaths.  Resources, including a Testing Site Locator and a Vaccine Provider Map, are available on the county’s website at  https://t.co/8iZNA5dcpr.

name: Allegheny County Health Department
tweet: There were 8 new deaths reported, 7 from an import of data from the Electronic Death Registration System. All deaths were in November 2021. One (1) person was in the 25-49 age group, one (1) person was in the 50-64 age group, and six (6) people were in the 65+ age group.
